{{On May 27, 2021, an individual calling itself "NebulousStar" posted a seemingly innocuous article to the SCP Foundation Wiki.}}
{{The events that followed were anything but.}}
@@ @@
@@ @@
{{For the past few years, I have been tracing this individual and its whereabouts. For years, I have watched, seeking a glimpse past its careful facade.}}
{{Today, I reveal the truth.}}
@@ @@
@@ @@
[[div class="blockquote"]]
[[include :scp-wiki:component:image-block name=https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/nebulousstar-author-page/nebpfp|caption=The last known photo of NebulousStar.|width=250px]]

[[module CountPages created_by="NebulousStar"]]
{{During its time on the SCP Wiki, NebulousStar has created countless pages. Of these, 21 remain.}}

{{Despite my best efforts, I could not recover those that were deleted. Though their content may be lost to time, I remember them. I remember the evils contained within, the things no human should know. It doesn't want you to know what it's done, but I, I know.}}

{{The following document catalogs its extant works.}}
[[/module]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
[[=]]
{{CONFIDENTIAL // LEVEL 2}}

{{Listed below are the known works of NebulousStar, categorized by type.}}

**{{SCP PAGES}}**

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-5643 SCP-5643]
{{An amateur exploration of addiction centering around a researcher and a rock.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6241 SCP-6241]
{{The story of an isolated paradise and its decline.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6642 SCP 6642]
{{A character piece about a hated alien.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6354 SCP-6354]
{{Lesbian ghost.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6982 SCP-6982]
{{An experimental article about memories and the future.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6431 SCP-6431]
{{A mediocre piece exploring a space under New Orleans.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6441 SCP-6441]
{{A silly foray into memetics.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6723 SCP-6723]
{{Arguably the best of the above, a notebook format about a dead child and a mysterious anomaly.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-8633 SCP-8633]
{{The first post in a while. A shortform piece that can't easily be explained without spoilers.}}

**{{TALES}}**

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/not-the-same-juno Not the Same Juno]
{{An old comic about the impacts of a monstrous transformation upon a researcher's social life.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/to-my-past-self To My Past Self]
{{An old and confusing deptcon entry.}}

**{{ARTWORK}}**

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:stars-character-drawings Star's Character Drawings]
{{A 2021 collection of artworks.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:stars-unfinished-stuff Star's Unfinished Stuff]
{{A 2021 collection of unfinished artworks.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:only-half-alive Only Half Alive]
{{A 2021 art exchange gift.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:ballpit Ball Pit]
{{An early 2022 work depicting SCP-6059.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:kittykotkot KOT art]
{{A 2022 piece depicting SCP-PL-KOT-J.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:flaming-sunset A Flaming Sunset]
{{A 2022 piece depicting SCP-6246.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:i-like-moths-and-stuff-so-i-made-this-i-guess Death's Head]
{{A late 2022 piece exploring style.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:nebsepicandcoolartexchangegift epic and cool art exchange gift]
{{A 2022 art exchange gift.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:ruinforetold ruin foretold]
{{An early 2023 piece.}}

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/art:nebulousstar-s-ae-2023 Neb's 2023 AE Gift]
{{A 2023 art exchange gift exploring light and shading.}}

**{{MISCELLANEOUS}}**

[https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/wilson-s-wildlife-adoption-gallery Wilson's Wildlife Adoption Gallery]
{{A co-authored page showcasing people's pets.}}
[[/=]]
[[/div]]

{{They know. But they do nothing about this.}}
[[/div]]

[[span style="filter: blur(0.5px);"]]{{Don't you remember what it's done? Or has it erased that, too? You remember the soup, the shift key, the **fish council**?}}[[/span]]

[[span style="filter: blur(0.75px);"]]{{Its broken promises,}}[[/span]]

[[span style="filter: blur(1px);"]]{{its project failures,}}[[/span]]

[[span style="filter: blur(1.5px);"]]{{its social constructions,}}[[/span]]

[[span style="filter: blur(2px);"]]{{all orchestrated to achieve one goal.}}[[/span]]

[[span style="filter: blur(5px);"]]{{THE END IS NEAR IT COMES TO FEED THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR THE END IS NEAR}}[[/span]]
@@ @@
@@ @@
Whoof, they're a little crazy; don't mind their ramblings. I'm Neb, and I like moths! If you need to contact me, I'm [[*user NebulousStar]] on Wikidot and nebulousstar on Discord.

Hmm, in case I disappear?

Well, if I disappear for six months or more, [[*user fish^12]] and [[*user parallelpotatoes]] can duke it out for custodianship of my works.

But why would I disappear?

[[div style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 0 #888;"]]
I'm not going anywhere.
[[/div]]
